"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/831132","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-01-31","<p>We have announced the creation of a new government-owned facilities management company that will take over the delivery of the prison Facilities Management services previously provided by Carillion. HM Prison and Probation Service will continue to work with prison Facilities Management providers, including the new company, as well as with prison governors, to secure significant improvements to these services.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2018-01-31T16:05:53.23Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/831132/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/831132/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/831132/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-01-26","Prisons: Repairs and Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether prison governors will be empowered to bring maintenance contracts back in-house.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","125140"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/831133","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-02-05","<p>The next Public Land for Housing programme annual report will be published shortly. This will give an update on homes constructed on public land.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2018-02-05T14:32:30.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/831133/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/831133/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/831133/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-01-26","Housing: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 25 January 2018 to Question 123693, if he will publish updated figures on the (a) number, (b) type and (c) tenure of homes under construction on public land since the publication of The Public Land for Housing programme 2015-20 annual report, published in February 2017.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","125141"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/831134","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-01-31","<p>Collecting data on joint enterprise cases is being considered as part of the Common Platform Programme. The Common Platform aims to provide a single case management system that will enable the sharing of evidence and case information across the Criminal Justice System.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-01-31T17:32:31.027Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/831134/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/831134/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/831134/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-01-26","Aiding and Abetting: Prosecutions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what plans his Department has to collect and publish statistics relating to the number of joint enterprise prosecutions.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","125142"
