"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/831158","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-02-05","<p>The Government recognises the challenges faced by existing leaseholders with onerous ground rents. We are currently considering how we can support existing leaseholders. A number of developers have introduced schemes to compensate individuals but we want to see this support extended to all those with onerous ground rents, including second hand buyers, and for customers to be proactively contacted. We will be checking on progress of these schemes and will consider measures that could be pursued to take action if necessary.</p><p>We will also be introducing legislation so that, in the future, ground rents on newly established leases of houses and flats are set at a peppercorn (zero financial value).</p><p>Leaseholders can seek free initial advice about ground rents and other leasehold issues via the Leasehold Advisory Service's (LEASE) website. Lease is a specialist advisory body funded by the Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government to provide assistance to leaseholders. Alternatively, a telephone appointment can be booked to speak to one of LEASE's legal advisors or advice can be sought by email.</p>","South Derbyshire","Mrs Heather Wheeler",,"2018-02-05T14:09:01.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/831158/answer","Biography information for Mrs Heather Wheeler","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/831158/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/831158/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-01-26","Ground Rent","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what steps his Department is taking to tackle leaseholds with doubling ground-rents; and what support his Department provides to tenants subject to those rents.","false","Biography information for Marsha De Cordova","Battersea","Marsha De Cordova","125166"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/831159","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-02-05","<p>The contracts which provide for the new night cover service commenced on 22 January, as planned. It was decided to reschedule the introduction of the service itself to allow more time for discussions with the suppliers and Approved Premises Managers, one-to-one consultation with staff potentially affected by the transfer and completion of recruitment and training activities. The new service will come into operation on 1 March.</p><p> </p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","125168","2018-02-05T16:42:09.157Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/831159/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/831159/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/831159/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-01-26","Approved Premises","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the commencement date is for the HMPPS Approved Premises (manned) Guarding Service contracts with Sodexo and OCS.","false","Biography information for Imran Hussain","Bradford East","Imran Hussain","125167"
