"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/830393","Department for Education","false","2018-01-30","<p>The department will devolve the adult education budget to Mayoral Combined Authorities and the Greater London Authority for 2019/20, subject to certain readiness conditions. We are working collaboratively with local areas to ensure people can gain the skills that meet both local and national needs and will be setting up Skills Advisory Panels to further inform local areas about the skills needs.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2018-01-30T17:42:37.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/830393/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/830393/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/830393/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-01-25","Training: Devolution","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what his policy is on the devolution of skills to directly elected mayors and combined authorities.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","124959"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/830394","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-01-30","<p>The consultations on the short-term accommodation grant and sheltered housing model closed on Tuesday 23 January 2018.</p><p>We will now consider all responses and the Government will provide a full response in the early summer of 2018. In the meantime we will continue to work with providers and local government on the details of the proposed funding models.</p>","South Derbyshire","Mrs Heather Wheeler",,"2018-01-30T15:43:52.833Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/830394/answer","Biography information for Mrs Heather Wheeler","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/830394/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/830394/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-01-25","Supported Housing: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, when he expects to respond to his Department's recent consultation on the funding of supported housing.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","124960"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/830395","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-02-02","<p>The information is not held in the format requested. Following a rigorous and independent evaluation of the clinically-led Ambulance Response Programme, in July 2017 the Department agreed NHS England’s recommendations to implement an improved ambulance performance framework. These changes improve responses to patients and the efficiency and resiliency of the ambulance service in the face of rising demand. All mainland National Health Service ambulance trusts are now operating against this new framework and the ambulance service on the Isle of Wight will do so from April 2018.</p><p> </p><p>We recognise that not all trusts are meeting the required standards, however NHS England and NHS Improvement are working closely with the service to assist them to effectively perform against these new requirements, and NHS England will undertake a review of the framework in spring 2018.</p><p> </p><p>Regional ambulance response time performance is available and is published monthly by NHS England. This can be found online at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/statistics/statistical-work-areas/ambulance-quality-indicators/" target="_blank">https://www.england.nhs.uk/statistics/statistical-work-areas/ambulance-quality-indicators/</a></p><p> </p><p>Response time performance by city or county area is not centrally collected.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2018-02-02T13:05:38.023Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/830395/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/830395/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/830395/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-01-25","Ambulance Services: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what estimate he has made of ambulance waiting times in each month in 2017 in (a) Lewisham, Deptford Constituency, (b) London and (c) England.","false","Biography information for Vicky Foxcroft","Lewisham, Deptford","Vicky Foxcroft","124961"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/830396","Department for Education","false","2018-01-30","<p>This is a matter for Her Majesty's Chief Inspector, Amanda Spielman. I have asked her to write to the hon. Member and a copy of her reply will be placed in the Libraries of both Houses.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2018-01-30T17:46:00.1Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/830396/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/830396/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/830396/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-01-25","Adult Education: Inspections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many providers of adult education in each region have not been inspected by Ofsted in the last three years; and what Ofsted grade each provider was given at the last inspection.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","124962"
